A reminder with "Provision 2" all students in the Bellevue Union School District receive a week’s worth of breakfast and lunches every Monday (schedule below) for FREE!

Please stop by your school and pick up meals MONDAY!

Kawana Springs Elementary: 10am-12pm

Taylor Mountain Elementary: 10:30am-12:30pm

Bellevue Elementary: 11am-1pm

Meadow View Elementary: 11:30am-1:30pm

Stay safe
~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~

¡Por favor pase por su escuela y recoja las comidas el LUNES!

Primaria Kawana Springs: 10 am-12pm

Primaria Taylor Mountain: 10:30 am-12:30pm

Primaria Bellevue: 11 am-1pm

Primaria Meadow View: 11:30 am-1:30pm

Mantenerse a salvo

Healthy Students Initiative of Sonoma County
August 25 at 8:01 AM ·

The pandemic, wildfires, social justice movement, and other current events have heightened the need to be sensitive to the effect these events can have on children.

Thankfully, Sonoma County Office of Education mental health team has curated a range of resources to help children cope with trauma and deal with their stress in positive ways, as well as resources for how to identify and help a child in crisis.

Access these resources at: https://www.scoe.org/traumahelp.

post_text:
Zoom is currently experiencing intermittent connection issues and we may not be able to start virtual classes on time today. While we hope that this issue will be resolved quickly, we are preparing for the possibility that we won't have live instruction today and will need to use other instructional tools. We are working on an alternative now, so please watch for an email from your teachers. We apologize for the inconvenience and continue to learn how to think on our feet during emergencies! Thank you for your understanding.

Zoom está experimentando problemas de conexión intermitentes y es posible que no podamos comenzar las clases virtuales a tiempo hoy. Si bien esperamos que este problema se resuelva rápidamente, nos estamos preparando para la posibilidad de que no tengamos instrucción en vivo hoy y necesitemos usar otras herramientas de instrucción. Estamos trabajando en una alternativa ahora, así que espere un correo electrónico de sus maestros. Nos disculpamos por las molestias y seguimos aprendiendo a pensar con rapidez durante las emergencias. Gracias por su comprensión.

post_text:
Our new Parent Portal for annual student data confirmation has been created. If we have your email on file you should have received an email. This is for annual notification we are required to provide, as well as annual notices you are required to review and approve. It is in place of hard copy "opening packets." Don't worry, if you still need an "opening packet" your school can print one for you.

parent portal link/enlace del portal principal: https://bellevueusd.asp.aeries.net/Student/LoginParent.aspx

Se ha creado nuestro nuevo portal para padres para la confirmación anual de datos de los estudiantes. Si tenemos su correo electrónico registrado, debería haber recibido un correo electrónico. Esto es para la notificación anual que estamos obligados a proporcionar, así como las notificaciones anuales que debe revisar y aprobar. Está en lugar de "paquetes de apertura" en papel. No se preocupe, si aún necesita un "paquete de apertura", su escuela puede imprimir uno por usted.

FRUGALFUN4BOYS.COM
Engineering Project for Kids: Build a Straw Roller Coaster! - Frugal Fun For Boys and Girls

CalServes Cool School Taylor Mountain Elementary
May 28 at 8:06 AM ·

Happy STEAM Thursday, COOL School! Missing out on theme parks? Today’s activity is just for you! Use your creative mind to build your own roller coaster. All you’ll need to do this is a cardboard box, straws, scissors, a hot glue gun, a ping pong ball, and an optional bowl at the end to catch the ping pong ball. Follow the link below for instructions and inspiration:

Feliz STEAM Thursday, COOL School! ¿Te pierdes los parques temáticos? ¡La actividad de hoy es solo para ti! Usa tu mente creativa para construir tu propia montaña rusa. Todo lo que necesitará para hacer esto es una caja de cartón, pajitas, tijeras, una pistola de pegamento caliente, una pelota de ping pong y un recipiente opcional al final para atrapar la pelota de ping pong. Siga el siguiente enlace para obtener instrucciones e inspiración:

https://frugalfun4boys.com/engineering-project-kids-build-straw-roller-coaster/

Local 1401 Fire Fighters, Toys For Kids
May 26 at 9:44 AM ·

The Toys for Kids, Local 1401 Firefighters, had the opportunity to reach out to kids in our community during social isolation. We always strive to bring joy to kids in need during the holidays, so it was extra special to bring a small amount of joy during this global health crisis! We shopped locally at Kaliedoscope and Village Art to put small gift bags together of toys and school supplies!

shared_text:
CALACADEMY.ORG
Animal Webcams

CalServes COOL School Bellevue Elementary
May 21 at 10:09 AM ·

Happy Thursday, COOL School families! We don’t know about you, but all this inside time is making us go a little crazy! Take a virtual step outside your home and check out these amazing animals at the California of Sciences. From the comfort of your home, you can watch penguins play, coral reefs, and so much more! Take a few minutes and follow the link below to be transported to beautiful nature. We hope you enjoy 

¡Feliz jueves, familias de COOL School! No sabemos sobre ti, ¡pero todo este tiempo interno nos está volviendo un poco locos! Dé un paso virtual fuera de su hogar y vea estos increíbles animales en la California of Sciences. ¡Desde la comodidad de su hogar, puede ver jugar a los pingüinos, los arrecifes de coral y mucho más! Tómese unos minutos y siga el siguiente enlace para ser transportado a la hermosa naturaleza. Esperamos que disfrutes 

https://www.calacademy.org/learn-explore/animal-webcams

Hello COOL School! For today's art project we have 3-D Umbrella Art. Follow along with the video below to create your very own 3-D umbrella. Community Action Partnership of Sonoma County

IMPORTANT INFO REGARDING CalFresh BENEFITS!

CalFresh recipients can now use their EBT cards to start purchasing groceries online at Amazon and Walmart. California is also working with many other retailers to expand the number of stores accepting EBT online in the weeks to follow. In addition, persons receiving CalWORKs will also be able to use their cash benefits to make purchases online at Wal-Mart.

Click on the link below for more information and resources:

https://www.getcalfresh.org

YOUTUBE.COM
Group STEAM Project for Kids: Cardboard City

CalServes Cool School Taylor Mountain Elementary
April 30 at 10:09 AM ·

Happy STEAM Thursday, COOL School families! For today’s project, I invite you to take all those extra cardboard boxes and recyclables (egg cartons, plastic containers, etc.) from around the house and construct your own cardboard city! This will allow you and your child to get creative and strategic with your building process! To make it even more realistic, add some color to your cities with paint or markers!

Feliz STEAM Thursday, COOL ¡Familias de la escuela! Para el proyecto de hoy, te invito a que tomes todas esas cajas de cartón extra y reciclables (cartones de huevos, recipientes de plástico, etc.) de la casa y construyas tu propia ciudad de cartón. ¡Esto les permitirá a usted y a su hijo ser creativos y estratégicos con su proceso de construcción! Para hacerlo aún más realista, ¡agrega un poco de color a tus ciudades con pintura o marcadores!

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3PUUdlDdJA8&feature=youtu.be

YOUTUBE.COM
5 ideas of amazing and easy greeting Cards

Calserves COOL School Kawana Elementary
April 28 at 11:01 AM ·

It's Tuesday! Time to let your creative side shine with some DIY Greeting Cards. Send a card in the mail to a family member or friend to spread some joy! You will need the following materials/tools: Colored paper, cardboard, decorative paper, self-adhesive, scissors, glue stick, thick thread, needle, felt pens, and pencils.
There are a variety of designs to choose from. Watch the video to pick your favorite ones and follow along with an adult!

¡Es martes! Es hora de dejar que su lado creativo brille con algunas tarjetas de felicitación. Envíe una tarjeta por correo a un familiar o amigx para difundir algo de alegría. Necesitará los siguientes materiales / herramientas: papel de color, cartón, papel decorativo, autoadhesivo, tijeras, barra de pegamento, hilo grueso, aguja, rotuladores, y lápices.
¡Hay una variedad de diseños! Vean el video para elegir sus favoritos y para seguir con un adulto.

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=OJvInlo7BAE

Larry is the IT Director. He's been working very closely with the Superintendent, principals and teachers as we move towards more online support for students. He also been working with teachers to prepare the classroom Chromebooks to be loaned out to students who don't have devices at home (as soon as we know when and how we'll tell you). His child is a year old. Larry works very hard and is amazing.

Larry es el director de TI. Ha estado trabajando muy de cerca con el Superintendente, los directores y los maestros a medida que avanzamos hacia un mayor apoyo en línea para los estudiantes. También ha estado trabajando con los maestros para preparar los Chromebooks del aula para que se presten a estudiantes que no tienen dispositivos en casa (tan pronto como sepamos cuándo y cómo se lo diremos). Su hijo tiene un año. Larry trabaja muy duro y es asombroso.

#SoCoEdStrong Sonoma County Office of Education

post_text:
Roger is our Director of Maintenance and Operations. He is always on the run, fixing things, getting people to fix things, meeting with people about things that need to be fixed and planning what needs to be fixed in what order. He's got a plan for district wide improvements and he's moving forward come rain or shine. I took this picture as he was taking supplies over to our Kawana Springs campus this morning. Roger's kids are teenagers. Roger is awesome at keeping staff and students safe!

Roger es nuestro Director de Mantenimiento y Operaciones. Siempre está huyendo, arreglando cosas, haciendo que la gente arregle cosas, reuniéndose con personas sobre cosas que necesitan ser arregladas y planeando qué necesita arreglarse en qué orden. Tiene un plan para mejoras en todo el distrito y está avanzando cuando llueva o haga sol. Tomé esta foto cuando llevaba suministros a nuestro campus de Kawana Springs esta mañana. Los hijos de Roger son adolescentes. ¡Roger es increíble para mantener seguros al personal y a los estudiantes!

#SoCoEdStrong Sonoma County Office of Education

As a reminder the BUSD Science/STEAM handbook, as well as project labels and judging rubric are on the BUSD website here: www.BUSD.org/science-fair The handbook and judging rubric continue to combine traditional science fair standards and the SCOE STEAM showcase rubric. Good luck to all of our students participating this year!
